         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">In one frame with <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408b"/>-<ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a408i"/>. The left part of the string hole space, which covers lines 2-4, is preserved. Although this fragment is not edited by <bibl><title corresp="ref:ogihara2009"/></bibl>, the word <hi>aśśe</hi> may be an indication that it belongs to the Bhikṣuṇī-Prātimokṣasūtra. Therefore, it is provisionally assumed that it belongs to manuscript A 415-416, not to A 406-408.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment"><hi>aśśe</hi>: this could be the attestation noted in <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegetal1931"/><citedRange>87</citedRange></bibl> as "Frgm.".</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment"><hi>/// ktsu ///</hi>: possibly <hi>(ā)ktsu(ne)</hi>.</note></p>
         </div>
